@d0<color=#ffff00>Log 147-2:</color>
<color=#ff8000>We took on a Doctor Weston from the colony who had fallen ill under mysterious circumstances. We had been cannibalizing the ship for spare parts to continue building the colony, but had not yet removed the medical bay so they sent him up to us to treat.</color>
@p9 @d0<color=#ff8000>All I know is red alert was issued and the captain sealed off the bridge with his personal command code and initiated the self destruct sequence.</color>
<color=#ff8000>Something went wrong and only 2 of the secondary generators blew. There were power surges but most of the ship is intact. If any U.C.H officers are reading this, you might be able to get some systems operational.</color>
@p9 @d0<color=#ff8000>You've no doubt already turned on the auxiliary generators. The gravity controls are on the other side of this room. Turn both switches to the on position, but to fully enable gravity you'll need to find the conduit bypass deeper in the ship. </color>
<color=#ff8000>You might be able to access the bridge if you search the captain's quarters for his personal over-ride.</color>
<color=#ff8000>I hear screams now. Nightmarish screams. I don't even blame the captain for wanting to destroy the ship. May the other ships of Project Eden find greener pastures...</color>

@d0<color=#00ffc6>Chief Medical Officer's Log:</color>
<color=#00ff00>I've analyzed the blood sample from Dr Weston. I've never seen anything like it before. The changes to his DNA are extensive. It is unlikely a cure can be found before he is irreversibly changed.</color>
<color=#00ff00>The alien virus appears extremely contagious and airborne. The host becomes contagious within 2 hours after exposure. Samples are too risky to keep.</color>
@p9 @d0<color=#00ff00>Dr Weston, or what's left of him, broke out of medical containment. I've put the whole crew quarters under lock down. I've been working on an experimental vaccine but haven't had time to test it yet. I've injected myself out of desperation, with hope that it will offer me some level of protection or slow down the progress of the virus.</color>

@d0<color=#00ffff>Log 471:</color>
The patient we brought up from the colony was more ill than we first thought. He's infected with some kind of alien parasite.
I've ordered him into medical quarantine in the medbay, as well as a full medical scan of the entire ship crew.
@p9 @d0<color=#00ffff>Log 472:</color>
Dr Weston broke out of medical quarantine, exposing the entire ship to the alien parasite he is carrying. I ordered a full medical lockdown while I make my way to the bridge.
If this infection... If this gets out of control I may have no choice but to destroy the ship. I can't allow it to escape and infect other colonies.

@d0<color=#00ffff>Log 44-8:</color>
Construction of the colony has been going slowly ever since our deconstructor blew out. Dismantling thrusters and RCS devices by hand takes 10 times as long.
I've ordered double shifts until we get the colony its own constructors and furnaces to become self sufficient.
@p9 @d0<color=#00ffff>Log 44-9:</color>
Well, this is it I suppose. The patient has escaped from medical quarantine, the captain locked down the ship, and the self destruct sequence failed. Power conduits blew all over the ship, crippling vital systems.
Power has begun to fail and the crew has begun to transform into the same nightmarish horrors as Dr Weston. It appears I am not to be spared this fate, either...

